%pyspark

# Load CSV files
crimes_file = sc.textFile('/user/root/crimes/atlanta')

# Extract the header
header = crimes_file.filter(lambda x: 'MI_PRINX' in x).map(lambda x: [x.strip().replace(' ', '_').lower() for x in x.split(',')])
field_count = len(header.collect()[0])

# Filter header and bad rows
crimes = crimes_file.filter(lambda x: 'MI_PRINX' not in x and ',' in x and len(x.split(',')) == field_count) \
 .map(lambda x: [x.strip() for x in x.split(',')])

# Define the table using the headers
sqlContext.registerDataFrameAsTable(sqlContext.createDataFrame(crimes, header.collect()[0]), 'crimes')

import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.phoenix.spark._
import java.sql.Connection
import java.sql.DriverManager

val input = "/user/root/crimes/atlanta"
val zkUrl = "docker.dev:2181:/hbase-unsecure"
val table = "CRIMES"
val pk = "OFFENSE_ID"

// Read CSV file, clean field  names
var df = sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header", "true").option("DROPMALFORMED", "true").load(input)
val columns = df.columns.map(x => x.toUpperCase.replaceAll(" ", "_"))
df = df.toDF(columns:_*)

val command = "create table if not exists " + table + "(" + columns.map(x => x + " varchar,").mkString("") + " constraint my_pk primary key (" + pk +")) salt_buckets=20"
var connection:Connection = null
  try {
    Class.forName("org.apache.phoenix.jdbc.PhoenixDriver")
    connection = DriverManager.getConnection("jdbc:phoenix:"+zkUrl, "", "")
    connection.createStatement().execute(command)
  } catch { case e: Throwable => e.printStackTrace }
connection.close()

df.save("org.apache.phoenix.spark", SaveMode.Overwrite, Map("table" -> table, "zkUrl" -> zkUrl))

paragraphs.text:
%sql 
select year, count(*) as count from (
  select
   neighborhood,
   regexp_extract(trim(split(rpt_date, "\/")[0]), "0*([1-9][0-9]*|0)", 1) as month,
   regexp_extract(trim(split(rpt_date, "\/")[2]), "0*([1-9][0-9]*|0)", 1) as year
  from crimes
) inner
group by
  year

%sql
select weekofyear(date), count(*) as count
from (
  select concat_ws('-',
    split(rpt_date, '\\/')[2],
    split(rpt_date, '\\/')[0],
    split(rpt_date, '\\/')[1]
  ) as date
  from crimes
) inner
group by weekofyear(date)

%sql
select * from (
  select
    neighborhood, count(*) as count
  from crimes
  group by neighborhood
) inner
order by count desc
